BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Det3da2iIZNLeB0KvRMej
SUMMARY:MOHAI Mercantile Literary Series - Seattle's Locks and Ship Canal
DTSTAMP:20260308T063048Z
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:MOHAI Mercantile is proud to host the official book launch even
	t for Seattle’s Locks and Ship Canal with local historians David B. Willia
	ms and Jennifer Ott! \\nThis portable guide from UW Press and HistoryLink 
	is an introduction to the engineering marvel of the Ballard locks\\\, and 
	a primer on the history of the ship canal. Hear from the authors about the
	 tumultuous history of one of Seattle’s defining projects\\\, and the dram
	atic changes it brought to the city’s economy\\\, neighborhoods\\\, and na
	tural environment. \\nDoors open at 6pm for music and mingling. Food and d
	rink available for purchase. \\nConversation and Q&A begin at 7pm\\\, foll
	owed by a book signing with the authors. \\nPreorder your copy through the
	 MOHAI Mercantile beginning in January 2026!\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/mo
	hai-mercantile-literary-series-seattles-locks-and-ship-canal/\n\nFrom MOHA
	I - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/mohai-mercantile-literary-series-seattles-locks
	-and-ship-canal/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:I7BPE4TjQ7yVZw1EYe49J
SUMMARY:March Magnolia After Hours at Seattle Makers
DTSTAMP:20260308T063048Z
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Our March After Hours is shaping up to be one of the most uniqu
	e experiences we’ve offered. Join us on March 24th from 6:00–8:30pm as Sea
	ttle Makers opens their 12\\\,000+ square feet of creative space exclusive
	ly for our Chamber community. \\nYou’ll get a guided tour through their in
	credible maker environment\\\, explore the endless possibilities for hands
	‑on creation\\\, and watch live t‑shirt printing in action. Even better — 
	you’ll walk away with a custom t‑shirt you made yourself\\\, a fun reminde
	r of the night. \\nAlong the way\\\, you’ll meet fellow Chamber members\\\
	, learn the story behind one of our most innovative member businesses\\\, 
	enjoy a little pizza\\\, and experience the kind of creative energy that m
	akes Seattle Makers such a standout in our community. \\nThis special grou
	p experience is offered to members for just $40 per person — a significant
	 Chamber‑only discount. \\n👉 Reserve your spot and join us for creativity\
	\\, connection\\\, and community.\n\nhttps://discovermagnolia.org/event/ma
	rch-magnolia-after-hours-at-seattle-makers/\n\nFrom Discover Magnolia
URL:https://discovermagnolia.org/event/march-magnolia-after-hours-at-seattl
	e-makers/
LOCATION:Seattle Makers\\\, 3012 16th Ave W\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98119\\\
	, United States
